      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Gavin discussed the whack-a-mole security issues with sensitive data being stored in memory, and I think this falls into that category. IMO this is more of a problem outside the scope of Bitcoin, but still important to be mindful of. Regardless, obscuring this data could slow down or prevent a potential attack. \n\nCan you propose how we could prevent this?\n",
